public class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        if (n < 1) return false;
        while (n % 3 == 0) {
            n /= 3;
        }
        return n == 1;
    }
}
```

### Explanation

This solution uses a while loop to continuously divide the input number `n` by 3 as long as it is divisible evenly (i.e., `n % 3 == 0`). If `n` is a power of three, this process will eventually reduce `n` to 1. If `n` is not a power of three, this process will leave a remainder greater than 1.

### Example Use Cases

```java
public static void main(String[] args) {
    Solution solution = new Solution();
    System.out.println(solution.isPowerOfThree(27)); // true
    System.out.println(solution.isPowerOfThree(0)); // false
    System.out.println(solution.isPowerOfThree(-1)); // false
}
```

